Operations Overview
Since its founding in 2005, Energy XXI has become one of the largest operators on the Gulf of Mexico (GOM) Shelf, utilizing the latest technologies, its existing infrastructure and its experienced staff to acquire, develop and exploit the upside potential of the region. Daily volumes averaged 42.9 thousand barrels of oil equivalent per day (72% oil) for the six months ended December 31, 2016.  Including operating nine of the largest fields on the GOM shelf, Energy XXI held interests in 616 gross producing wells, 439,294 net developed acres, and 57 producing fields at its fiscal year-end of December 31, 2016.
Visit each major field to the right to learn more about the asset and how it contributes to the success of our company.






